<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sampras Quits Canadian Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, July 25 (Xinhua) -- American Pete Sampras, winner of
the Australian Open and Wimbledon championship, withdrew from the
Canadian Open tennis tournament to be held in Montreal on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The world tennis number one had aggravated a previous arm
injury during practice, said ATP Tour spokesman Greg Sharko in
Toronto.
</P>
<P>
Sharko was quoted as saying: "He started to feel some
irritation toward the end of Wimbledon. He resumed practising this
week at his home in Tampa (Florida) and that's when he started to
feel the pain."
</P>
<P>
The Canadian Open is considered to be the major warm-up event
for the US Open in New York.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
