<HEADLINE> EMEAP Convenes In Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 25 (Xinhua/OANA) -- The governors of 11 central
banks and monetary authorities in the Asia/Pacific region
expressed their hope here today for increased cooperation to
stabilize the regional currency markets in times of emergency.
</P>
<P>
They discussed the recent developments in currency markets in
East Asia during the one-day closed-door meeting of the second
governors' meeting of the Executives' Meeting of East Asia and the
