<HEADLINE> Britain Pledges not to Evacuate Montserrat </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 25 (Xinhua) -- The British government has pledged
that it would not evacuate the Caribbean island of Montserrat,
which has been devastated by a series of powerful volcanic
eruptions.
</P>
<P>
British Foreign Office minister Liz Symons said in a statement
issued this afternoon: "I wish to make it clear that the British
government have no intention of evacuating Montserrat in the
present circumstances."
</P>
<P>
The British government made the announcement following press
speculation that Britain was considering evacuating the tiny
island in eastern Carribean.
</P>
<P>
"We are committed to helping the people of Montserrat by
providing emergency aid now, and through a long-term program which
will maintain the economic and social viability of the island in
the future," Symons said.
</P>
<P>
"But the decisions on the island's future must include
consultation with its people. The Chief Minister is visiting UK
next month. and we intend to hold discussions on a whole range of
issues," she said.
</P>
<P>
It is reported that volcanic eruptions on the British territory
have killed about 20 people, making hundreds of people homeless.
</P>
<P>
Earlier this month, the British government decided to grant
some 41 million pounds (about 68 million U.S. dollars) in a bid to
help local residents. 
</P>
</TEXT>
