<HEADLINE> Graf Father Back to Jail </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, July 25 (Xinhua) -- Tennis star Steffi Graf's father
Peter will go back to prison next Monday to serve out his jail
term for tax evasion, a report said from Mannheim, Germany.
</P>
<P>
The 59-year-old Peter Graf, who was sentenced to three years
and nine months in January, was released while both sides
considered lodging appeals. No appeal was made and Graf returns to
prison next week, local court said.
</P>
<P>
Graf was found guilty of avoiding pay 7.5 million U.S. dollars
in tax by a system of front companies which concealed 26 million
U.S. dollars of the tennis player's earnings from 1989 to 1993
from the tax authorities.
</P>
<P>
The Graf family has to pay 11 million U.S. dollars in back
taxes.  
</P>
</TEXT>
