<HEADLINE> Italian Wins 19th Stage after Two Disqualifications </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 25 (Xinhua) -- Mario Traversoni of Italy won
Friday's 172 kilometers 19th stage of the Tour de France from
Montbeliard to Dijon after the first two riders were disqualified
for infringements.
</P>
<P>
Dutchman Bart Voskamp and Jens Heppner of Germany crossed the
sprint first and second. They broke away from a leading group of
14 about 30 kilometers from the line but were disqualified for
committment of faults.
</P>
<P>
The win goes to third Traversoni. Jan Ullrich of Germany
retained the overall lead after he came in with the group more
than 14 minutes behind the sprinters. 
</P>
</TEXT>
