<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 1630 GMT, July 25 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PETALING JAYA, MALAYSIA -- The Association of Southeast Asian
Nations (ASEAN) Friday hoped that a peaceful solution to the
Cambodian crisis would enable the country to join ASEAN and
fulfill the vision of a 10-member ASEAN as envisaged by its
founding fathers.
</P>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY -- The United Nations has gotten a positive
response from Iraq in cooperation on the task of getting rid of
alleged Iraq's weapons of mass destruction, visiting new
U.N. chief weapons inspector Richard Butler said here Friday.
</P>
<P>
MOSCOW -- The damage caused by an accident at the Mir orbital
station in June is preliminarily estimated at 125 billion roubles
(about 20 million U.S. dollars), the Itar-Tass news agency
reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
DHAKA -- Bangladesh's police Friday fired tear gas to disperse
a group of Muslim fundamentalists who brought out a procession
defying a ban on rallies and processions around Baitul Mukarram
Mosque, the national mosque of the country.
</P>
<P>
CAIRO -- Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak will hold talks with
Palestinian National Authority President Yasser Arafat on the
Middle East peace process Saturday, the Egyptian Middle East News
Agency quoted Foreign Minister Amr Moussa as saying Friday.
</P>
<P>
NEW DELHI -- India's Bihar Chief Minister Laloo Prasad Yadav
resigned Friday shortly after an arrest warrant was issued
against him for his alleged involvement in a multi-crore rupee
scandal, the Press of Trust of India (PTI) reported.
</P>
<P>
TOKYO -- A U.N. Conference on Disarmament Issues ended Friday
in Sapporo, northern Japan, with differences remaining over
whether to continue focus on nuclear arms reduction or to face the
danger posed by conventional arms.
</P>
<P>
PHNOM PENH -- Cambodian Second Prime Minister Hun Sen and
U.S. special envoy Stephen Solarz Friday agreed on three
principles for solving the current crisis in Cambodia, including
respect for the Paris peace accord and the results of the 1993
election. 
</P>
</TEXT>
