<HEADLINE> Turkish Troops to Return Home from Albania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, July 25 (Xinhua) -- Turkish troops who joined a
multinational protection force to maintain security and stability
in Albania will return to Turkey next week, a military statement
said here today.
</P>
<P>
The statement from the Turkish General Staff said that the
troops of the multinational protection force started to withdraw
from Albania on July 20 under a plan, adding that a contingent of
781 Turkish troops will return to Turkey between July 29 and
August 1.
</P>
<P>
The Turkish troops have made contributions to providing
security and stability in Albania, said the statement.
</P>
<P>
The Turkish troops went to Tirana, capital of Albania, in
April to take part in the "Mission Alba" organized by the United
Nations in a bid to protect Tirana, the Tirana Airport and the
northern part of Albania.
</P>
<P>
The mandate of the multinational protection force, set up
according to the U.N. decision to provide distribution of
humanitarian aid, to install security atmosphere in the region and
to provide security for the general elections in Albania, will
expire on August 12. 
</P>
