<HEADLINE> Bahrain Raps EU Protectionist Measures </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, July 25 (Xinhua) -- Bahrain has lashed out at the
European Union (EU) for its recent protectionist measures against
the exports of the Gulf Cooperation Council (GCC) members.
</P>
<P>
First Deputy of the Bahraini Chamber of Commerce and Industry
(CCI) Hassan Zine al-Abidine was quoted by the local daily
Al-Ayyam as saying that the measures were the most harmful
sanctions against the development of the economic ties between
the EU and the GCC states.
</P>
<P>
The GCC groups Bahrain, Kuwait, Oman, Qatar, Saudi Arabia and
The United Arab Emirates.
</P>
<P>
The delegation representing the GCC and the CCI raised during
its talks with the European Commission in Brussels and the
European Parliament in Strasbourg recently the issue of "the
carbon tax" and the customs tariff increases on the aluminium and
petrochemical exports of the GCC members to the EU.
</P>
<P>
The delegation urged the EU officials to offer preferential
treatment to the GCC exports in reciprocation with the treatment
received by the European exports to the GCC member states.
</P>
<P>
It called for increasing the European investments and more
joint ventures in the GCC countries as well as launching a free
trade zone between the two sides.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the CCI official underlined the importance of
approving the single customs tariff draft by the GCC members as
the EU attributes its refraining from concluding any agreement
with the GCC members to the GCC's lack of a unified tariff.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
