<DOCNO> XIE19970726.0028 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-25 18:43 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Israeli Secret Agents Infiltrate Into Palestinian </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, July 25 (Xinhua) -- The Israel Defense Forces (IDF)
dispatched an undercover unit to Tulkarm in the Palestinian
self-rule area late Thursday to arrest an Islamic Jihad activist,
reported the state-run Israel Radio.
</P>
<P>
Unidentified military sources were quoted as saying that the
IDF secret agents, dressed as Arabs, arrested Mahmoud Madawi in
the town and took him away.
</P>
<P>
Madawi, who escaped from an Israeli jail together with a
Palestinian inmate, had been serving a sentence of 17 years'
imprisonment allegedly for stabbing an Israeli and planning
terrorist attacks.
</P>
<P>
Palestinian officials pointed out that Madawi's arrest by the
IDF unit is a violation of the peace accord signed by the Israeli
government and the Palestine Liberation Organization.
</P>
<P>
Tulkarm is one of the six cities that came under the
Palestinian self-rule under the Oslo 2 agreement signed between
Israel and the Palestinians in 1995. The Palestinian National
Authority has the sole jurisdiction in the cities.
</P>
<P>
This is the first time the IDF took no notice of the
Palestinian jurisdiction to launch a secret invasion into the
autonomous area.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the IDF today declared Qalqilya, another self-rule
town in the West Bank, a "closed military area," and entry by
Israelis is prohibited. Nablus and Jenin will continue to be
closed to Israelis. 
</P>
