<HEADLINE> 500 Hectares of Forest Burned in Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, July 25 (Xinhua) -- More than 500 hectares of forest
were destroyed in a fire in southern Turkey's Antalya, the
semi-official Anatolia News Agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
The forest were burned out in a fire which took place Monday
in the Guver Canyon of Antalya, a province on the Mediterranean
coast. The economic losses caused by the fire are not immediately
available.
</P>
<P>
Tuncay Neyisci, an environmental expert from the Mediterranean
University was quoted as saying that not only trees but also
animals were lost in the fire.
</P>
<P>
He said that the fire-hit Guver Canyon is a natural habitat
of the endangered fallow deer and the mountain goat, adding the
canyon and the falls were also affected by the fire.
</P>
<P>
The forestry authorities should adopt new concepts and take
modern technologies in fighting forestry fires, Neyisci said.
</P>
<P>
He argued that the wind and fire resistant trees, such
as cypress, should be planted in the mountains around the
country.
</P>
<P>
Forest fires cause heavy economic losses to Turkey every
year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
