<HEADLINE> UNDP to Organize International Conference on Governance </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, July 25 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations
Development Program (UNDP), Which prioritizes governance as a key
area of its development assistance, is organizing an international
conference on governance at the United Nations from July 28-30,
1997.
</P>
<P>
The event, organized by the UNDP as a result of increasing
concern worldwide over finding effective and local solutions to
poverty, inequity and human insecurity issues, will bring together
hundreds of high-level ministers, parliamentarians, mayors,
non-governmental organizations and representatives from media,
private sector and development organizations.
</P>
<P>
They will review a number of key governance issues of concern
to developing countries, including democratization,
administrative, market reform and human rights protection.
</P>
<P>
The meeting will provide a forum for local and national leaders
to identify obstacles and review successes in governance programs
in their countries. Specific topics to be debated include: ways of
increasing involvement of women and civil social organizations in
government; how mayors are positioning cities as important players
in the global economy; how to combat corruption; how governments
can improve fiscal, macro-economic and development aid
management; judicial reform and decentralization of local
government. 
</P>
