<HEADLINE> Chinese Vice-Premier Meets Russian Foreign Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PETALING JAYA, Malaysia, July 26 (Xinhua) -- Chinese
Vice-Premier and Foreign Minister Qian Qichen and Russian Foreign
Minister Yevgeny Maksimovich Primakov today evaluated highly the
strategic cooperation partnership between their two countries.
</P>
<P>
At their meeting here this afternoon, the two ministers noted
that the state visit paid to Russia by Chinese President Jiang
Zemin in April this year was very successful.
</P>
<P>
They said Russian President Boris Yeltsin will make another
trip to China later this year, when the fifth summit between the
two countries will take place in Beijing, a Chinese Foreign
Ministry spokesman told a press briefing.
</P>
<P>
"The exchange of visits by leaders of the two countries has
vigorously pushed forward the Sino-Russian strategic cooperation
partnership and the good-neighborly relations between the two big
countries have also exerted an important and positive influence on
international relations," the ministers were quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
Qian and Primakov in their meeting exchanged views on
international and regional issues and "reached broad consensus,"
the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
The two maintained that the world today is facing many complex
problems, which should be properly addressed through peaceful
consultations and negotiations. Both China and Russia are
permanent members of the U.N. Security Council and share identical
or similar views on many international issues, they noted.
</P>
<P>
"They should further strengthen consultation and cooperation
and together play an active role in maintaining world and regional
peace and stability," the spokesman quoted the ministers as
saying.
</P>
<P>
The two ministers are here to attend the ASEAN Regional Forum
and Post Ministerial Conference scheduled for July 27-29.
</P>
