<HEADLINE> Nepali Commercial Bank Resources Rise Slowly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, July 26 (Xinhua) -- The total resources of Nepali
commercial banks increased at a sluggish rate of 3.2 percent to
90.25 billion rupees (about 1.58 billion U.S. dollars) during the
first nine months of the fiscal year 1996-97.
</P>
<P>
The growth rate was 17.3 during the same period of the previous
fiscal year, said the latest Economic Survey for Fiscal Year
1996-97 that ended on July 14.
</P>
<P>
During the first nine months of the 1996-97 fiscal year, total
deposits rose by 8.6 percent to 77.3 billion rupees (1.35 billion
dollars), as against an increase of 11.1 percent in the same
period of the previous fiscal year, the survey said.
</P>
<P>
During the period, a total of 12 bank branches were
established, bringing the total number of bank branches in Nepal
to 460.
</P>
<P>
The number would be 479 if the 19 branches of the Agriculture
Development Bank which are doing commercial transactions were also
included, the survey said.
</P>
<P>
Nepal now has a total of 11 joint-venture commercial banks, the
survey added.  
</P>
</TEXT>
