<HEADLINE> China Wins First Day of Challenge Tourney in Tianjin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, July 26 (Xinhua) -- Both world women's runner-up Wang
Nan and men's third place Yan Sen beat their Swedish rivals apiece
on the first day of the Tianjin stop in the Chinese international
table tennis challenge tournament on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Wang Nan, who won the women's singles silver medal of the 1997
World Championships in April, made an easy victory over Pernilla
Pettersson 21-12, 21-10, 21-19.
</P>
<P>
Pen-holder Yan Sen came from a first set back to overplay Peter
Karlsson, world men's doubles runner-up this year, 17-21, 21-12,
21-12, 21-18.
</P>
<P>
The Swedish veteran took the first set, mainly relying on his
steady loop drives. But the young Chinese controlled the next
three sets with flexible services and powerful strokes to seal the
triumph.
</P>
<P>
"I didn't play well today," Yan Sen said.
</P>
<P>
Wang Tao, member of China's world team champion, and Cheng
Hongxia Sunday will play Dmitry Mazunov of Belarus and Asa
Svensson of Sweden respectively to finish the Tianjin tournament.
</P>
<P>
The Tianjin competition was the second stop of the China's
challenge. The first stop was held last week in Changshu, Jiangsu
Province. 
</P>
