<HEADLINE> Cermeno Retains His WBA Crown </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, July 26 (Xinhua) -- Antonio Cermeno of Venezuela
Saturday beat Japan's Yuichi Kasai to retain his World Boxing
Association (WBA) junior featherweight title in Yokohama, Japan.
</P>
<P>
Cermeno knocked his challenger down two minutes 35 seconds into
the 12th and final round, reports reaching here said.
</P>
<P>
It was a repeat performance for Cermeno, who defeated the same
opponent by a unanimous decision in December last year in Las
Vegas, Nevada.
</P>
<P>
It also was Cermeno's sixth defence of the title he wrested
from Wilfredo Vasquez of Puerto Rico in May 1995, stretching his
record to 28 wins, including 17 KOs, and one defeat.
</P>
<P>
For Kasai, it was his third attempt at a world title. The WBA's
fifth-ranked boxer now stands at 24 wins, including 16 KOs, four
defeats and a draw. 
</P>
