<HEADLINE> CPPCC Chairman Stresses Improvement of Work Style </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 26 (Xinhua) -- The need to improve work styles
and on-the-job efficiency with a combination of theory,
performance review and research was stressed in a speech delivered
today by Li Ruihuan, Chairman of the National Committee of the
Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC).
</P>
<P>
Addressing the 21st Session of the Eighth Standing Committee of
the CPPCC national committee, Li noted that the Chinese Communists
have a tradition of studying theories, for actions might be taken
blindly without the guidance of theories.
</P>
<P>
He said that many of the problems that are presently showing up
in the process of developing the socialist market economy involve
the theoretical vs. the practical approach to issues.
</P>
<P>
Also, the chairman mentioned the importance of summing up
experience, saying it is a necessary link between perception and
rational understanding of an event.
</P>
<P>
Two big leaps in the history of the Chinese Communist Party
(CPC) were the results of reviewing prior experiences, according
to Li, who is also a standing committee member of the political
bureau of the CPC central committee.
</P>
<P>
For example, the summarization of the Seventh National Congress
of the Chinese Communist Party had laid a solid foundation for the
victory of the New-Democratic Revolution. And the review of
historical experience made at the Third Plenary Session of the
Eleventh CPC central committee blazed a new trail for developing
socialism with Chinese characteristics.
</P>
<P>
The chairman noted that summing up an event is not a simple
matter, but rather a complex process of eliminating what's false
and holding on to the truth, and discarding superficial details
while selecting the essential under the guidance of the Marxist
theory.
</P>
<P>
Li highlighted the importance of systematic research, which
focuses on soliciting ideas and public opinion and converting it
into concrete, practical plans.
</P>
<P>
He criticized those departments for either doing insufficient
research or conducting improper research in their work, noting
that research constitutes the fundamental work method of all
leading officials. 
</P>
</TEXT>
