<HEADLINE> 70 Kilograms Heroin Seized in Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, July 26 (Xinhua) -- Turkish gendarme police seized
70 kilograms of pure heroin in eastern Turkey, the semi-official
Anatolia News Agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
The agency said that the gendarme police stopped a truck at
Sevindik village in Gurpinar town of Van province bordering Iran
and found the heroin in the vehicle. However, the agency did not
report when the heroin was confiscated.
</P>
<P>
The heroin was brought from Pakistan via Iran and was
planned to be sent to Diyarbakir, center of southeastern Turkey,
said the agency.
</P>
<P>
The report said that the police had detained the driver of the
truck in connection with the drug trafficking.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, the Turkish police seized 4.4 tonnes of heroin,
accounting for 40 percent of the world's total haul, 12.3
tonnes of hashish, 233 kilograms of opium, 13 kilograms of
cocaine and 1,157 kilograms of base morphine. 
</P>
</TEXT>
