<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Guangzhou Prohibits Use of Styrofoam Dinner Containers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, July 26 (Xinhua) -- The production, sale, or use of
styrofoam dinner containers has been officially prohibited in
Guangzhou, capital of south China's Guangdong Province.
</P>
<P>
All hotels, restaurants, factories, and individuals are now
required to use the dinner sets made from plant fibre which
dissolve naturally, instead of the foam plastic kind that are
widely used for fast food.
</P>
<P>
Known as "white pollution," the styrofoam boxes do not
decompose in landfills.
</P>
<P>
The relevant departments of the Guangzhou government are
working out details of the regulation to ban such products in the
city. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
