<HEADLINE> 10,000 DWT Dock to Be Built for Southeast China Port </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, July 26 (Xinhua) -- China's coastal Fujian Province
will spend nearly 200 million yuan (24 million US dollars) on a
dock project at Sandu'ao in Ningde Prefecture.
</P>
<P>
Ningde has an 878-km coastline, a third of Fujian's total. Of
the five coastal prefectures, only Ningde lacks a 10,000 DWT
dock. Its existing shipping capacity couldn't meet the economic
development needs of Ningde.
</P>
<P>
In a feasibility report, experts said that a large-scale
deepwater wharf should be built there because of its natural
conditions. It could have an annual handling capacity of 500,000
tons, and include deepwater berths, warehouses, and other
facilities.
</P>
<P>
Ningde has been proposing that it build a wharf since 1996.
</P>
</TEXT>
