<DOCNO> XIE19970726.0075 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> North China City Sets Bottom Line for Needy Workers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, July 26 (Xinhua) -- This capital city of north
China's Hebei Province had given a total of 35.14 million
yuan-worth (4.3 million US dollars) of subsidies to 17,000 needy
workers by the end of May.
</P>
<P>
Some workers experienced financial difficulties and hardships
when the enterprises which employed them were running at a loss or
going bankrupt.
</P>
<P>
The city government raised money from local unemployment
insurance savings, personal income tax, revenue, and other fees to
set up an aid-the-needy fund.
</P>
<P>
Shijiazhuang had collected 35.95 million yuan (4.33 million US
dollars) by the end of May to help the workers whose incomes of
the past six months were lower than the local minimum wage or
bottom line cost of living. 
</P>
