<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Local Highway Patrolman Effective in Stopping Crime </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, July 26 (Xinhua) -- China's new highway patrolmen, who
came about as part of a reformed traffic police system, have prove
their worth in stopping crime.
</P>
<P>
Highway fatalities on one experimental section in Yunnan
province, in the southeast, dropped 55 percent since policemen
started patrolling it on January 1.
</P>
<P>
They have handled 26,000 traffic violations and 169 accidents
during the first half of the year.
</P>
<P>
Highway patrolmen are part of a new branch of the traffic
police. They handle a broader range of problems than traditional
policemen who stand in police boxes and write accident
reports. They have the right to use firearms if necessary to
arrest people suspected of serious crimes.
</P>
<P>
Patrolmen began working on all of Yunnan's highways on July
1. Many cities in China have also adopted this new system.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
