<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hong Kong's Last Evening Paper to Close Down </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 26 (Xinhua) -- The New Evening Post, the only
evening newspaper now in Hong Kong, will close down as from Sunday
because of publication-related difficulties, its Board of
Directors announced today.
</P>
<P>
In a statement carried by the paper's last issue, the board
said the New Evening Post has been welcomed by the public since it
 started publication in 1950.
</P>
<P>
However, the paper has come to a deadlock -- irresolvable
financial difficulties. A total of seven local evening newspapers
have closed down one after another in the past 13 years. The
decline of the evening newspapers began in the late 1970s as TV
was becoming more popular, gaining the upper hand in intense
market competition. 
</P>
</TEXT>
