<HEADLINE> More Overseas-Funded Enterprises reported in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 26 (Xinhua) -- The metropolis of Shanghai had
16,420 overseas-funded enterprises by the end of June, a 3.1
percent rise from the end of last year, with more than 44.2
billion yuan in registered capital, an percent of 3.8 percent.
</P>
<P>
On average, 82 overseas-backed companies became operational
every month. Shanghai has a total of 1,045 overseas-funded
projects with more than 10 million US dollars each in
investment. Some are expected to help improve industrial mix in
Shanghai and promote the development of newly-emerged pillar
industries.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, businesses in the service sector has become
increasingly popular. So far, nearly 32 percent of the
overseas-funded companies in Shanghai are in this sector.
