<HEADLINE> Tianjin Sees Sharp Growth in Overseas Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, July 26 (Xinhua) -- This port city of north China has
seen a sharp increase in overseas cash inflow in the first half of
this year, topping two billion US dollars in contractual value.
</P>
<P>
According to latest statistics released by the city's
Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation Commission, the city has
approved 471 jointly-funded projects by overseas investors since
the beginning of this year. a figure ranking second in the country.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai remains the leader in attracting overseas investors to
China, according to official sources.
</P>
<P>
The numerous overseas investors, including 190 multinationals
in processing industry, have built nearly 10,000 joint ventures in
Tianjin over the past years, involving in a total of 20 billion
dollars in overall investment.
</P>
<P>
The total industrial output value of the city's joint ventures
in production has reached 40 billion yuan in the first half of
this year, with their pre-tax income hitting 2.3 billion yuan, an
increase of 22 percent on a year-on-year basis.
</P>
<P>
Wang Shuzu, director of the city's foreign trade and economic
commission, said that the city's overseas investment will increase
by 15 billion dollars in the coming five years.
</P>
<P>
"Foreign-funded enterprises that have kept expanding in the
city over the past few years will play a key role in the local
economy before the end of this century," he said.
</P>
<P>
The official said that the city is doing more to improve its
investment environment by building more infrastructure projects
and basic facilities, such as ports, highways, and
telecommunications systems.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the city will help foreign-funded enterprises with
the process of localization, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
