<HEADLINE> South Koreans Take Five Titles at Pacific Rim Judo Opener </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, July 26 (Xinhua) -- The Pacific Rim Judo Championships
opened Saturday with South Koreans grabbing five of eight gold
medals in the first-day competition.
</P>
<P>
South Korea's Park Moon Soo won the men's 78kg category gold,
the first of eight awarded golds on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Park's teammates Bae Jae Chan and Park Sung Kun took two other
golds in the men's 86kg and the 95kg respectively. While Japanese
Naoto Yabu won the title in the men's over 95kg category.
</P>
<P>
South Koreans also took two gold medals in the women event. Kim
Hwa Soo won the 61kg and Lee Hyun Kyung, gold medalist at the
Atlanta Olympics last summer, also bagged a gold medal in the over
72kg.
</P>
<P>
Japan's Chigusa Minami won the 66kg while China's Li Yanfu took
home the gold medal in the 72kg category.
</P>
<P>
Some 160 Judo players from 13 countries and regions including
China, Australia, the Philippines, South Korea, Japan, the Guam,
Chinese Taipei, China Hong Kong, the United States and host Macao
are attending the two-day championships.  
