<HEADLINE> More Trees Planted In Northeast Chinese Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARBIN, July 26 (Xinhua) -- China's Heilongjiang province
planted 270,000 hectares of forests this spring and raised
seedlings on 10,000 hectares, as volunteers have planted 85
million trees.
</P>
<P>
Leaders in Heilongjiang province place great importance on the
afforestation work. Daqing city has launched a Green Ecology
Project, spending 60 million yuan on 15,000 hectares of forest.
</P>
<P>
In an effort to plant more trees, some key projects have been
emphasized. In the forest resources project, for instance, fuel
forests grew more than three-fold to 15,000 hectares this
spring. In Mulan County, people used waste land and the bend of a
river to plant fuel trees. The county's wicker handicrafts have
been exported abroad, and have become a backbone industry.
</P>
<P>
New technology has been used for these projects. In Tsitsihar
city, dry farming technology has been popularized, with 3,000
hectares of trees and seedlings planted in vessels, an increase of
30 percent over last year.
</P>
<P>
More money had been spent on planting trees. Cities and
counties alone have invested 249 million yuan on afforestation.
</P>
