<TEXT>
<P>
PETALING JAYA, Malaysia, July 26 (Xinhua) -- China today called
on the parties in Cambodia to maintain the country's political
institutions, including King Norodom Sihanouk's dignity and status.
</P>
<P>
"We hope that the Cambodian parties continue to uphold the
position and dignity of King Sihanouk and maintain the country's
existing structure of political institutions," Chinese
Vice-Premier and Foreign Minister Qian Qichen said in meeting with
Cambodian Foreign Minister Ung Huot here this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
The two foreign ministers exchanged views on the situation in
Cambodia, where fighting broke out between the forces of First Prime
Minister Norodom Ranariddh and Second Prime Minister Hun Sen on July 5
and 6, resulting in the ouster of Ranariddh.
</P>
<P>
Qian also urged that the parties, "in the spirit of national
reconciliation, solve their problems through peaceful means and thus
enable the country to embark on the road to peace, stability and
development."
</P>
<P>
He noted that the peace in Cambodia was hard-won and he expressed
concern over the recent developments in the country.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese vice-premier stressed his country's view that the
Cambodian question should be solved by the Cambodian people themselves
and other countries should not interfere.
</P>
<P>
He expressed his appreciation of the effort made by the Association
of Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN) to solve the Cambodian question.
</P>
<P>
Ung Huot promised to continue maintaining the authority of King
Sihanouk and work for the country's stability and reconstruction
according to the country's constitution and laws.
</P>
<P>
Qian is here to attend the ASEAN Regional Forum (ARF) and Post
Ministerial Conference scheduled to start here tomorrow while Ung
Huot, whose country enjoys observer status in the ASEAN, participated
in the opening and closing sessions of the ASEAN Ministerial Meeting
which was closed yesterday and will attend the ARF. 
</P>
