<DOCNO> XIE19970726.0090 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> AIDS Cases on Increase in Zanzibar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, July 26 (Xinhua) -- There has been a marked
increase in the number of AIDS infections in Zanzibar, in which
1,465 people were reported to have been infected with the HIV
virus during the last 11 years, said a report reaching here
today.
</P>
<P>
A total of 919 people were confirmed to have developed full
blown AIDS since the first AIDS patient in Zanzibar was reported
in 1986, according to the report.
</P>
<P>
Manager of the Zanzibar AIDS Unit, Hamad Juma Haji, told
reporters in the town of Zanzibar on Friday that the most
affected areas are the Zanzibar Urban and West districts.
</P>
<P>
He attributed the trend to the tendency by the people to
ignore the preventive measures outlined by health officials.
</P>
<P>
According to statistics, the pandemic has more affected
females than males, especially those in the age group from 20 to
29 years, which is 31.7 percent of the total AIDS cases
diagnosed.
</P>
<P>
Haji added that males account only for 14.8 percent of all
cases diagnosed for AIDS in Zanzibar. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
