<HEADLINE> Guangdong Economy Recovers from Two-Year Drop </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, July 26 (Xinhua) -- Economic performance in south
China's Guangdong Province has improved by close to 10 percent in
the first half of the year, showing a recovery from the sharp drop
of the past two years.
</P>
<P>
Industrial production rose 19 percent, four percentage points
higher than that for the same period last year, while the retail
price index increased only 0.1 percent.
</P>
<P>
The province reported 32.6 billion US dollars worth of exports,
a year-on-year increase of 26.89 percent, accounting for about 40
percent of the national total. Investment in fixed assets is also
going up. 
</P>
