<HEADLINE> More Sino-foreign Ventures For Beijing This Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 26 (Xinhua) -- Another 379 Sino-foreign joint
ventures opened in Beijing in the first half of the year, making
China's capital a new hot-spot for foreign investment.
</P>
<P>
The city attracted over 940 million US dollars worth of
overseas funds, 20.5 percent more than for the first six months of
last year. The city's foreign investment had been declining since
1994, but this year marked the change.
</P>
<P>
According to Nong Xiqun, director of the Beijing Foreign Trade
Commission, foreign funds are focusing on infrastructure,
residential buildings, finance, and high-tech businesses.
</P>
<P>
The Beijing-Badaling Expressway project, at a cost of 320
million US dollars, has been approved by the commission, Nong said.
</P>
<P>
Many multinationals like Japan's Canon are looking for business
opportunities here, and 138 of the world's 500 biggest businesses
have invested in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Nong said that the city government has done its best to improve
the investment environment. Departments have simplified the annual
company exam procedures, and have set up a complaints office for
joint ventures. 
</P>
</TEXT>
