<HEADLINE> Tianjin's Telecom Network Digitalized </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, July 26 (Xinhua) -- With the disconnection of the last
200 analogue-mode transmission lines from the telecom network in
Tianjin, an industrial and port city in north China, China's first
digital telephone network was born.
</P>
<P>
According to a senior telecom official, now that the entire
network is digitalized, "every node within the net can operate all
kinds of new data transmission services, as well as other
value-added telecom services on various telecom band-width as the
clients required."
</P>
<P>
He praised the move as one of the steps to improve the city's
overall investment environment.
</P>
<P>
Before 1993, Tianjin's telecom network was mainly
analogue. Large-scale construction and huge financial input in
recent years has thoroughly revamped the technical level of the
system. 
</P>
</TEXT>
