<HEADLINE> Shanghai Sets its Pollution Control Goal for 2000 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 26 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai municipality has set
itself the goal of meeting state emission standards by the end of
this century.
</P>
<P>
It plans to focus on controlling the discharge of pollutants
and improving water and air quality this year, as part of that.
</P>
<P>
In the past year, the metropolis already made some progress in
pollution controls, with 91.4 percent of the urban families using
liquefied petroleum gas and more than a half of the urban districts
meeting noise standards.
</P>
<P>
In addition, smoke and dust emissions are also under control,
and some 40 percent of the urban sewage has been treated. Green
coverage has further climbed one percentage point to 17 percent.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, the city has also moved 15 factories with serious
pollution problems, and 100,000 automobiles have been installed
with exhaust treatment equipment. 
</P>
</TEXT>
