<HEADLINE> Hong Kong's Total Retail Sales Up in May: Statistics </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 26 (Xinhua) -- The total retail sales in Hong
Kong reached 19.7 billion U.S. dollars in May of this year, an
increase of 10 percent compared with the same month of last year,
according to official statistics reported here today.
</P>
<P>
The increase indicated a major recovery for the retail sector
in Hong Kong, experts here believe.
</P>
<P>
The experts expect growth to be stronger in the succeeding
months from June, given the buoyant mood of the public over the
handover.
</P>
<P>
Comparing January to May this year with the same period in
1996, total retail sales rose 8 percent, the Census and statistics
Department of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region said in
a report.
</P>
<P>
Compared with a year ago, sales of motor vehicles continued to
record a significant increase in May, by 21 percent, while sales
of jewelry, watches, clocks and valuable gifts also surged, by 17
percent, the statistics showed.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, sales of other commodities also recorded rises of
various magnitudes in both value and volume.  
</P>
</TEXT>
