<HEADLINE> Compiling of Macao Encyclopedia in Full Swing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, July 26 (Xinhua) -- The compiling of Macao's first
encyclopedia is in full swing and the work is expected to be
finished by the end of this year.
</P>
<P>
Since the editing work started in early 1996, editors have
finished 2,500 out of the 3,800 set entries, and the rest will be
completed by the year end, the Macao Daily News reported today.
</P>
<P>
Under an agreement signed by the Macao Foundation and the
Encyclopedia of China Publishing House (ECPH) in 1995, the Macao
Encyclopedia is jointly compiled by the two organizations.
</P>
<P>
While the ECPH provides technical support in editing and
styling, the Macao Foundation is responsible for the formation of
an editing committee. The book will be published next year.
</P>
