<HEADLINE> Chinese NPC Vice-Chairwoman Meets With Chadian Guests </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 26 (Xinhua) -- Chen Muhua, vice-chairwoman of the
Standing Committee of the Chinese National People's Congress (NPC)
and chairwoman of the All-China Women's Federation, met with a
women's delegation from Chad in the Great Hall of the People here
today.
</P>
<P>
The Chadian delegation is led by Hadje Halime Deby, wife of the
Chadian president and honorary chairwoman of the Chadian Women's
Promotion and Development Association.
</P>
<P>
Chen said the visit will help enhance the exchanges and
understanding of the women of the two countries and advance the
development of friendly bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
Chen also briefed the guests on the situation with the women's
work in China.
</P>
<P>
Deby said that she is ready to continue working for the
expansion of the contacts and exchanges between the women of the
two countries.
</P>
<P>
The Chadian women visitors have come to China as guests of the
All-China Women's Federation. 
</P>
