<HEADLINE> Philippine House Speaker to Meet Muslim </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, July 26 (Xinhua) -- The speaker of the Philippine House
of Representatives, Jose de Venecia, is scheduled to meet the
country's Muslim rebel leaders today in Mindanao, the southern
Philippines.
</P>
<P>
De Venecia will hold talks with Al Haj Murad and Ghadzali
Jaafar, vice chairmen of the separatist Moro Islamic Liberation
Front (MILF), in Camp Abubakar, the MILF's biggest camp in
Maguindanao province, the Philippine News Agency said.
</P>
<P>
De Venecia was quoted as saying the meeting is intended to push
the stalled MILF-government peace negotiations.
</P>
<P>
The MILF froze its low-level peace talks with Manila late last
month soon after the military overran its second biggest camp in
Cotabato province.
</P>
<P>
No particular agenda was laid down by de Venecia for today's
meeting with MILF leaders, leaving many observers speculating that
the speaker's peace initiative has something to do with his
political ambition for the presidency.
</P>
<P>
De Venecia has openly declared his intention to run for the
presidency in next year's elections. Like other presidential
aspirants, the speaker is also seeking President Fidel Ramos'
"blessing" as his successor.
</P>
<P>
The MILF and the Muslim extremist Abu Sayyaf are the two
remaining Muslim insurgent groups still fighting the government.
</P>
<P>
The MILF, a splinter group of the bigger Moro National
Liberation Front (MNLF), has refused to accept the MNLF-Manila
peace accord signed last year. But the group began its own peace
talks with Manila this January. 
</P>
</TEXT>
