<HEADLINE> Business Guidebook to be Published in Uganda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, July 26 (Xinhua) -- A business guidebook prepared for
four years will be published soon, "The New Vision" reported
today.
</P>
<P>
Bruce L. Mazzie, head of Private Enterprise Support, Training
and Organizational Development Project, said the book, "a
practical guide to running business in Uganda", will provide
service to micro and small enterprises whose development is
encouraged by the Ugandan authorities.
</P>
<P>
Publishing such a guidebook will meet "rampant hunger for
business information", Mazzie said.
</P>
<P>
According to Mazzie, the book consists of three sections: the
first will contain a directory of all the organizations, projects
and other facilities that provide assistance to business; the
second will give a quick guide of the offices in government that
a business must register with; while the third will include terms
of laws under which business must operate and comply with.
