<HEADLINE> Bean Curd Festival In Its Chinese Birthplace </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, July 26 (Xinhua) -- The humble and homely bean curd will
star in its own cultural festival to be held in September by the
Anhui Provincial government, east China.
</P>
<P>
The China Bean Curd Cultural Festival 1997, sponsored by the
Ministry of Internal Trade, will start on September 6 in Huainan
city, which is regarded as the birthplace of bean curd, a
traditional source of protein for both rural and urban Chinese and
a staple part of their diet, and one of the health foods popular
among the Chinese.
</P>
<P>
The five previous festivals, which started in 1992, have
resulted in more than 40 large-scale business activities centering
on this food, and 3.7 billion yuan (446 million US dollars) worth
of business.
</P>
<P>
The festival will also include an international symposium on
this by now globally-popular food. 
</P>
</TEXT>
