<HEADLINE> Kenyan Muslims Demonstrate Against Jewish </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, July 26 (Xinhua) -- More than 10,000 Muslims in Kenya
demonstrated on Friday in port city Mombasa in protest against
alleged Jewish blasphemy of the Islamic religion, according to a
"East African Standard" report today.
</P>
<P>
The placard-waving demonstrators called upon the Israeli
ambassador to kenya to apologize publicly to Kenyan Muslims and
asked the Kenyan government to sever diplomatic ties with Israel
immediately.
</P>
<P>
The demonstrators walked to the Israeli consulate in the city,
burning an effigy of Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu
and the Israeli flag.
</P>
<P>
Chanting anti-Israeli slogans, the demonstrators marched from
the consulate to the Provincial Commissioner's office to present
a memorandum, demanding, among other things, the immediate
suspension of diplomatic relations with Israel.
</P>
<P>
The memorandum said that the suspension should be put in force
pending an apology by the Israeli government to Muslims and the
taking of appropriate measures against the Israeli woman who
defiled the image of Prophet Muhammad in Israel.
</P>
<P>
The demonstrators said that the action by the Israeli woman
was similar to that of Salman Rushdie who authored the "Satanic
Rushdie" and on whose head Iran put a price. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
