<HEADLINE> China's First Individual Property Insurance Policy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 26 (Xinhua) -- A Shanghai insurance company has
begun to offer China's first individual property insurance policy,
in conjunction with the forthcoming 8th National Games.
</P>
<P>
The one-year insurance policy is for property loss or damage
and has a face value of 88 yuan (about 10 US dollars). Maximum
compensation runs as high as 94,000 yuan.
</P>
<P>
Officials at the Shanghai Branch of the People's Insurance
Company (Group) of China (PICC Group) say that any resident of
Shanghai, whether Chinese or foreigner, can buy the insurance
policy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
