<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Two New Companies Help Businessmen Scout New Positions </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 26 (Xinhua) -- Two new companies here have
provided many high-level management personnel for successful
businesses to help the fast economic development.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai Talent Company for Managers and Factory Directors,
which is only 20 months old, has information on nearly 11,000
people. It represents 677 firms and has recommended 242 people to
high positions.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai Business Talent Company, which is only two months
old, has also succeeded in scouting over 10 senior officials for
business groups like Shanghai Industries and Dongfang
International.
</P>
<P>
"The establishment of the talent scout businesses has
challenged the long-adopted government-designated system of
official appointments," said Gu Dingguo, chairman of Shanghai
Business Talent.
</P>
<P>
The two companies primarily provide general managers, chief
engineers, and chief accountants for Chinese and overseas firms.
</P>
<P>
According to a recent survey, at least 27 percent of business
managers want to change their jobs.
</P>
<P>
Over 86 percent of new job seekers give as their major reason
for changing: "realizing their utmost potential". 
</P>
</TEXT>
