<HEADLINE> Hingis Enters Semis of Bank of West Tournament </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 25 (Xinhua) -- Top seed Martina Hingis savored
another victory on Friday, sailing into the semifinals of the Bank
of the West women's tennis tournament in California.
</P>
<P>
By downing Linda Wild 6-1, 6-7 (7-9) and 6-3, Hingis, the
youngest top-ranked woman player of the century, improved her
singles record to 48-1 this year.
</P>
<P>
After an easy win in the first set, Hingis, defending champion
of the 450,000 US dollars tournament, was broken four times in the
second set with poor services before losing the tiebreaker 7-9.
</P>
<P>
And even in the final set, Hingis only reasserted her dominance
in the later stage by ralling back from 1-3 to win the last five
games in a row.
</P>
<P>
In other quarter actions, sixth-seeded Conchita Martinez
recorded her first win in 12 meetings against Monica Seles by
downing her nemesis 7-6 (7-5), 6-4 in one hour and 52 minutes.
</P>
<P>
Also advancing were third-seeded Amanda Coetzer who defeated
No. 7 Kimberly Po 7-5, 6-4 and fourth-seeded Lindsay Davenport who
won over Elena Likhovtseva 7-6 (7-2), 6-3.
</P>
<P>
In the semifinals on Saturday, Hingis will face Davenport and
Martinez plays Coetzer. 
</P>
</TEXT>
