<HEADLINE> Premier Li Peng Meets With Hong Kong Guests </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIDAIHE, July 26 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Premier Li Peng and his
wife Zhu Lin met with Aliced Chang Yung Tsung, member of the
National Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative
Conference (CPPCC) and general manager of the Yung Shing
Enterprise Co., Hong Kong, here Friday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Cheng was accompanied by her son Christopher Cheng during the
meeting.
</P>
<P>
Cheng told the premier about her impression on the celebrations
marking the 50th anniversary of the founding of the Inner
Mongolian autonomous region.
</P>
<P>
Li said that the autonomous region's achievements showed the
correctness of the central government's policies toward the
country's ethnic groups.
</P>
<P>
Li praised Cheng for her love for the motherland and Hong Kong
and her concern and support for the economic construction in the
inland areas over the years.
</P>
<P>
Li said that various celebrations marking Hong Kong's return to
the motherland were conducted in a warm, grand and orderly way and
everybody is satisfied.
</P>
<P>
He expressed the belief that under the leadership of the
government of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (HKSAR),
Hong Kong will surely be able to maintain long-term stability and
prosperity. 
</P>
</TEXT>
