<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka Holds Favorable Trade Balance Over France </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, July 26 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lanka holds a favorable trade
balance over France mainly due to the rapid growth of garment
exports in recent years, local press reported today.
</P>
<P>
Sri Lanka exported 531 million U.S. dollars worth of
commodities to France while only 227 million U.S. dollars of
commodities were imported from France last year.
</P>
<P>
Sri Lanka's exports to France were mainly garments,
agricultural and food products and manufactured equipment while
imports from France were textile and accessories, aircraft,
industrial equipment and consumer goods.  
</P>
