<HEADLINE> New Albania Cabinet Takes Office </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, July 25 (Xinhua) -- Albania's new government led by the
Socialist Party took office today, vowing to restore security and
revitalize the economy after five months of chaos.
</P>
<P>
The new ministers led by Prime Minister Fatos Nano were sworn
in by new President Rexhep Mejdani at the Palace of Brigades.
</P>
<P>
Earlier today, Nano named his left and center-left coalition
government, more than one month after the elections in the
trouble-hit Balkan nation.
</P>
<P>
The government comprises five parties and 22 ministers,
including the prime minister and fellow Socialist Bashkim Fino,
who was named deputy prime minister.
</P>
<P>
Fino was appointed caretaker prime minister in March as Albania
was lurching towards anarchy.
</P>
<P>
Mejdani, 53, a former physics professor who joined the Socialist
Party only last year, was elected by the parliament on July 24 and
immediately asked Nano as the leader of the parliamentary majority
to form a cabinet.
</P>
<P>
Albania has been ruled by a Socialist-led national unity
government since March, when former President Sali Berisha's
Democratic Party government stepped down at the height of unrest
sparked by the collapse of pyramid investment schemes. 
</P>
