<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Investment up in Southeast Chinese Coastal City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAMEN, July 26 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong investment in Xiamen, a
special economic zone in southeast China's Fujian Province,
increased markedly in the first half of the year at 345 million US
dollars, up 8.5 percent.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong funded 173 projects in the first half, up 55 percent
from the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
Most investment is going to industries in the form of exclusive
backing, one economist said, and some of it is an increase to
expand production after good results were achieved.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong is Xiamen's largest investor. It began investing in
service trades on a small scale in 1981, but that increased
remarkably to more than a billion US dollars from 1986 to 1990.
</P>
<P>
The economic co-operation reached a high point from 1991 to
1995 at 5.8 billion US dollars for 1,132 projects.
</P>
<P>
At present, 90 percent of Hong Kong-funded ventures are showing
profits. 
</P>
</TEXT>
