<HEADLINE> Argentina's Industrial Output Increases </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, July 25 (Xinhua) -- Argentina's industrial
production increased by 7.9 percent in the first half of this
year, signaling the end of economic recovery and the beginning of
expansion, Industry, Commerce and Mining Secretary Aleito Guadagni
said today.
</P>
<P>
Production in June increased by 0.8 percent over the same month
last year, the 15th consecutive month of growth.
</P>
<P>
Sectors showing the highest growth in the first half were
agricultural chemicals (42 percent), motor vehicles (41 percent),
tires (24.4 percent) and building materials (22 percent).
</P>
<P>
Industry, Commerce and Mining Secretary Aleito Guadagni said
the figures signaled the recovery process was over and the
country was now in an expansionary phase. 
</P>
</TEXT>
