<HEADLINE> Summer Grain Purchase In North China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, July 26 (Xinhua) -- North China's Hebei Province
purchased 1.3 billion kg of grain from farmers by July 15, two
percent more than the state quota.
</P>
<P>
The province set a historic record both in the total output of
wheat and per unit output, and is expected to get in 12.9 billion kg
of grain this year, 10 percent more than last year.
</P>
<P>
To protect farmers' interests, the provincial government
purchased other grains at protective prices after farmers had met
the state grain quota and built more grain warehouses.
</P>
<P>
Finance, price control, industry, and commerce departments
joined hands in helping farmers and in preventing the use of IOUs.
</P>
