<HEADLINE> Venezuelan Oil Firms to Invest in Environment Protection </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CARACAS, July 25 (Xinhua) -- Maraven and Lagoven, two branches
of the Petroleos de Venezuela (PDVSA) state oil firm, will invest
a sum of 154 million U.S. dollars in the next 10 years in
environmental protection projects.
</P>
<P>
Maraven will come up with 93.75 million dollars and Lagoven
60.4 million dollars for environment protection in the country,
PDVSA was quoted today by the press.
</P>
<P>
Maraven seeks to reduce the production of waste products and
diminish the impact of its operations on environment, while
Lagoven will develop two environmental projects to make its
production of hydrocarbons meet the environmental standards.
</P>
<P>
Lagoven hopes to reduce the emissions of sulphuric dioxide
after the projects are completed in 1998. 
</P>
