<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Large Projects with Overseas Fund Rises in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 26 (Xinhua) -- Projects each with more than 10
million US dollars in overseas investment in Beijing rose
remarkably over the past six months in spite of the slower inflow
of total overseas funds into the Chinese capital.
</P>
<P>
Between January and June, Beijing approved 29 big projects with
committed overseas investment reaching 764 million US dollars,
today's China Daily reported.
</P>
<P>
Overseas funds of these projects accounted for 81.45 percent of
the city's gross overseas investment during the six months,
compared to 63.9 percent in the same period of last year, the
paper quoted Zhao Xinxin, an official with the Beijing Municipal
Foreign Economic and Trade Commission, as saying.
</P>
<P>
Average overseas capital per project climbed to 2.47 million US
dollars from 1.6 million a year earlier.
</P>
<P>
Investment from multinationals maintained its momentum with 17
new projects launched in the first half this year, promising 85.87
million US dollars in investment.
</P>
<P>
By the end of June, 138 multinationals among the world's top
500 companies had settled in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Zhao said statistics also indicated overseas investors
expanded their investment fields by beefing up funding in
agriculture, infrastructure construction, hi-tech, tourism,
housing and financial information consulting sectors.  
</P>
</TEXT>
