<HEADLINE> UNICEF Promises China a grant of 100 Million U.S. Dollars </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 26 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations Children's Fund
(UNICEF) promises China a grant of more than 100 million
U.S. Dollars for its children during the rest of the century,
according to the "China Daily".
</P>
<P>
Co-operative projects - nutrition improvement, provision of
safe drinking water fostering healthy living habits among rural
people and upgrading maternal and child health care - will be
carried out.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the national immunization program for children
will be strengthened.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese Government signed a World Declaration on Children
Survival, Protection and Development in 1991 and developed its
National Program for Children Development.
</P>
<P>
The program outlined 10 specific targets, including a one-third
drop in infant death rate by 2000, a 50 per cent reduction in
mortality rate of pregnant and lying-in women and a 50 per cent
decline in moderate and serious malnutrition among children under
five years old. 
</P>
