was preceded by 140 million US dollars worth contracts signed
earlier in the year with regions including Liaoning, Hebei and
Qinghai provinces and the Inner Mongolia Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
China currently ranks as Ericsson's second largest marketplace
worldwide, with the company employing over 3,000 people in 19
regional offices and nine joint ventures.  
