<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGCHUN, July 26 (Xinhua) -- The No. 1 Motor Works &AMP; Volkswagen
Co. Ltd., the largest of its kind in China, exported 15,000 air
valve cylinder bodies to Germany in the first half of this year.
</P>
<P>
It's the first time the Sino-German joint venture, built in
1991, has exported its auto parts. Earlier, it exported 300 Jetta
Brand cars to southeast Asian countries, said a company official.
</P>
<P>
This suggests that the company is shifting from truck
production to car production, he added.
</P>
<P>
The company, built with an investment of 10.7 billion yuan, has
a designed annual production capacity of 150,000 cars.
</P>
<P>
Since 1991, the market share of its principal product, Jetta,
has grown gradually and climbed to 9.1 percent in June.
</P>
<P>
To further raise its competitiveness, the company invested 1.6
billion yuan to import a 20-valve cylinder production line from
Germany, which turns out 270,000 cylinders each year.  
