<HEADLINE> FBI: Olympic Bombing Targets Law Officers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 25 (Xinhua) -- Law enforcement officers were
the target of the Olympic bombing in Atlanta last year, the U.S.
Federal Bureau of Investigation (FBI) said today for the first
time.
</P>
<P>
The 911 call made shortly before the bomb went off was intended
to bring officers to the scene, the Associated Press quoted Jack
Daulton, the agent in charge of the investigation, as saying.
</P>
<P>
Daulton said that the bomber knew that officers would rush to
the Olympic park to move people to safety.
</P>
<P>
The 911 caller had warned, "There is a bomb in Centennial Park.
You have 30 minutes." And the bomb went off in just 22 minutes.
</P>
<P>
The bomb exploded in the park on July 27 last year during the
Olympic Games, killing one woman and injuring more than 100
others, including several officers. 
