<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New York Stocks End Mixed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, July 25 (Xinhua) -- Stocks on Wall Street meandered
in a narrow range today, producing little changes in most major
indexes, but snapping a streak of record highs by the Dow Jones
industrial average.
</P>
<P>
The Dow fell 3.49 points in the final minutes to 8,113.44. The
blue-chip measure, up 222.98 for the week, never moved more than
40 points in either direction all day.
</P>
<P>
The market did not react too much to the day's economic news.
Experts said that investors are more concerned about next week's
readings on employment costs, which typically account for
two-thirds of a product's price.
</P>
<P>
The Commerce Department reported this morning that orders for
big-ticket manufactured goods perked up a surprising 2.3 percent
in June, while the National Association of Realtors reported that
sales of existing homes slipped 2.6 percent.
</P>
<P>
Advancing issues barely outnumbered decliners on the New York
Stock Exchange, where the volume was down from Thursday's pace to
519.61 million shares.
</P>
<P>
The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500-stock list fell 1.51 to 938.79, and
the NYSE composite index fell 0.51 to 486.80. Both measures closed
at record highs Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The American Stock Exchange composite index rose 0.75 to 637.80,
and the Nasdaq composite index rose 0.50 to 1,569.63. 
</P>
</TEXT>
