<DOCNO> XIE19970726.0212 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China, Cook Islands Establish Diplomatic Relations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 26 (Xinhua) -- The People's Republic of China and
the Cook Islands have established diplomatic relations at
ambassadorial level effective from July 25, 1997.
</P>
<P>
Huang Guifang, China's ambassador to New Zealand, and Iaveta
Short, Cook Island's senior commissioner to New Zealand, signed a
joint communique concerning the establishment of diplomatic ties
between the two countries on behalf of their respective
governments in Wellington on Friday.
</P>
<P>
According to the communique, the Chinese government supports
the people of the Cook Islands in their efforts to achieve their
goals in the areas of social, economic and cultural development.
</P>
<P>
The Cook Islands government recognizes that there is only one China
in the world and that Taiwan is an inalienable part of the
territory of the People's Republic of China. The Cook Islands
recognizes the government of the People's Republic of China as the
sole legal government of China and it reaffirms the long-standing
policy not to enter into official relations with Taiwan in any
form.
</P>
<P>
The two governments have agreed to exchange ambassadors as soon
as possible, according to the communique.
</P>
<P>
Tang Guoqiang, spokesman for the Chinese Ministry of Foreign
Affairs, noted that China is willing to establish and develop
friendly relations of cooperation with all countries in the world
on the basis of the Five Principles of Peaceful Co-existence.
</P>
<P>
The forging of diplomatic relations between China and the Cook
Islands not only is in the fundamental interests of the two
peoples, but also is conducive to the prosperity and stability in
this region, Tang said.
</P>
<P>
China will, as always, contribute to the development of
friendly relations of mutual benefit and cooperation with the
South Pacific nations and to the maintaining of peace and
stability in the Asia Pacific region, the spokesman said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970726.0213 </DOCNO>
