<HEADLINE> More Agricultural Commodities Bases For Central China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, July 26 (Xinhua) -- China will spend 69.5 million
yuan building 13 bases producting agricultural commodities in
central China's Hunan Province this year.
</P>
<P>
They will include eight grain producing centers, two quality
cotton growing centers, two for oil-bearing crops, and one
sugar-bearing crop base.
</P>
