<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai Sees Speedy Economic Growth in First Half </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 26 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai's economy maintained a
sustained, speedy and sound development in the first half of this
year.
</P>
<P>
The latest statistics indicated that in the first six months
this, China's largest industrial and financial center witnessed a
good summer harvest, steady industrial production and thriving
markets. Also, its foreign trade developed further and the
economic mix was better adjusted, amidst slowing price rises.
</P>
<P>
According to the Shanghai Municipal Statistics Bureau, the
gross domestic product (GDP) of the city in the first six months
totaled 154.4 billion yuan, a year-on-year rise of 13.7 percent,
or four percentage points higher than the national average.
</P>
<P>
The city also enjoyed a record grain harvest totalling 578,000
tons, a rise of 11.2 percent over last year. The per-ha yield
averaged 4,057 kg, the same as that of last year.
</P>
<P>
The industrial turnover in the period hit 269.1 billion
yuan-worth, up 14.4 percent, of which the state sector posted a
rise of 11.5 percent; the collective sector, up 14.7 percent; and
ventures with foreign capital, up 27.2 percent. The production-sales
ratio in the period was 96.6 percent higher than last year.
</P>
<P>
The service industry witnessed rapid growth, with an increase
of 23.9 percent in the period; its proportion to GDP increased to
44.6 percent. Of the various categories, finance and insurance
registered the fastest growth, 53 percent.
</P>
<P>
Exports in the period came to 7.322 billion yuan-worth, a rise
of 12.7 percent.
</P>
<P>
The people's living standards also improved and incomes
increased in the period. The average worker's monthly salary was
884 yuan, up 11.6 percent after deducting price rises. The cash
income of farmers averaged 3,420 yuan a month, up 13.8
percent. The balance of saving deposits hit 232 billion yuan at
the end of June, a net increase of 45.2 billion yuan compared to
that at the beginning of this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
