<HEADLINE> Portuguese PM Visits Uruguay </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MONTEVIDEO, July 25 (Xinhua) -- Portuguese Prime Minister
Antonio Guterres arrived here today Brazil for a three-day
official visit to Uruguay.
</P>
<P>
Uruguayan President Julio Maria Sanguinetti and Guterres had a
private meeting today before attending the signing ceremony of the
agreement on promotion and reciprocal protection of investments in
both countries.
</P>
<P>
At a press conference after the ceremony, Sanguinetti said that
this is the first visit to Uruguay by a Portuguese prime minister,
which will contribute to developing relations between both
countries and the two regional blocs -- Mercosur and the European
Union.
</P>
<P>
Guterres said that through the visit he wants to develop a
framework of relations stronger than in the past, taking advantage
of the dynamic interrelation between the European Union and
Mercosur.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that it is necessary for Portugal to transform a
relation of great cultural and historical identity into a
practical relation, into relations between the enterprises,
between the societies, between the cultures.
</P>
<P>
Both countries will sign some other agreements during the visit.
</P>
<P>
The Portuguese prime minister is scheduled to visit the
Legislative Palace and meet with Uruguayan Vice president Hugo
Batalla, Montevideo Mayor Mariano Arana and with some Uruguayan
businessmen this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
On Saturday, Guterres will travel to the city of Colonia, in
west Uruguay, where he will participate in the inauguration of the
remodeling work of the Portuguese Period Museum.
</P>
<P>
Trade between Portugal and Uruguay is limited with the balance
of trade tilting to Uruguay. Uruguayan imports from Portugal were
3 million U.S. dollars while its exports to the European country
were 6 million dollars. 
