<HEADLINE> Construction of Ningxia Fertilizer Project Begins </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YINCHUAN, July 26 (Xinhua) -- The Ningxia Chemical Plant
recently commenced construction of a large chemical fertilizer
project in Yinchuan, capital of the Ningxia Hui Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
The key state project, which will cost an estimated 1.58
billion yuan, will produce 300,000 tons of synthetic ammonia and
520,000 tons of urea annually upon completion.
</P>
<P>
A natural gas pipeline with a 40,000 cu.m. annual transport
capacity will link the new facility with suppliers in the
Shaanxi-Gansu-Ningxia Basin.
</P>
<P>
The plant's current annual production capacity stands at
300,000 tons of synthetic ammonia and 520,000 tons of urea.
</P>
<P>
The Ningxia Chemical Plant expects to raise annual earnings to
1.5 billion by the end of the century, with accompanying annual
profits and taxes rising to over 100 million yuan.  
